\begin{theorem}
Let $x$ be any object.
Then $x$ is an extended-real Float of format $\beta$, $p$, $e_{\text{min}}$, $e_{\text{max}}$
if and only if $x$ is an element of the set [[FLOAT_NUMBER]]($\beta$, $p$, $e_{\text{min}}$, $e_{\text{max}}$).
