\begin{theorem}
If $e_{\text{min}}\in\ZZ$ and $e_{\text{max}}\in\ZZ$,
then $v\in\FF(\beta,p,e_{\text{min}},e_{\text{max}})$ is normal if and only if
there exists a $x\in\RR$ such that $x=v$ and $\beta^{e_{\text{min}}}\leq x\leq\beta^{e_{\text{max}}}(\beta - \beta^{1-p})$.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}[Proof sketch]
This simply ``unrolls'' the definition of ``normal'' floating-point
numbers to match the case specified by the hypotheses that
$e_{\text{min}}\in\ZZ$ and $e_{\text{max}}\in\ZZ$.
\end{proof}

